Great progress team. Thought for future iteration of dashboard/kpi’s: Much of what’s happening in these early days of web3 is finance/speculation-based, hence the stock market references in dashboards. DAO’s, as they mature, will be doing the work found in non-profits, trad companies, trad manufacturers, community development, etc. To support this maturation, we need to think about how to bring DAO’s to the masses, the next billion users. Finance and trading markets intimidate the average person. We’ll want to promote progress, societal benefit, and activity in the reporting metrics for DAO’s. These things are relatable to the DAO-curious.

I fully agree long term. My main concern would be stretching appeal too wide may make our impact thin. Focusing on a more understood niche and focusing on perfecting a high quality impact should be priority #1. One of the main reasons facebook was able to integrate so well into society was its methodical system of focusing on one college/ market at a time. Another great historical example would be Alexander the great who was great at conquering a large amount of land and societies (markets), but his fatal flaw was lacking deep and strong integration within each unique society. To build one strong successful community it has to be a systematic targeting of smaller communities and markets. This may increase User Acquisition Cost, but I strongly believe it will strengthen retention.

**Set some clear direction for the DAO Sphere. Added some mockup outlines and inspiration to the Figma "Brief" section!**

**TL;DR**
- DAO Sphere != DAO Race
- DAO Sphere is the infrastructure that contributors & DAOs use to collaborate with other DAOs. It’s a directory.
- Users see a DAO’s KPIs, bio, & links to its product and community
- KPIs are charted and provide signal. Using this we’re able to standardize DAOs and determine what makes a DAO “good.”
- These KPIs will be used for the DAO Race v2. The next iteration of decentralized investing.
- We’re rebranding to Hyang’s style

Refer to this for more info: https://discord.com/channels/916751469678579784/925928766235103292/927336395486421103

What if we put emphasis on the Ecosystem as a whole? A DAO signs up once and gets access to all products.

When a DAO joins the ecosystem >

1. Gets added to DAO Race as default ‘Invisible’. Not in running for investment. But adds to benchmark data when ranking DAOs on our side. Option to become ‘Visible’ contestant and request investment.
2. Added to Directory - to collaborate with other DAOs and interact with contributors.
3. Added to Bounty Market (when It's built) to delegate tasks.

Access to Community Support is reserved for Race winners.

The con of this approach would be having no super focused USP to attract a specific audience. Ecosystem may be a little vague as a USP.
